struct
A struct is a user-defined type that contains a collection of named fields/properties. 
It is used to group related data together to form a single unit. 
Any real world entity that has a set of properties can be represented using a struct.


let take an example how to decleared struct

type Employee struct {  
    firstName string
    lastName  string
    age       int
}
--------------------------------------------------------------
Data Type In Golang

Data type in go language can specify the type of data that a valid Go variabe can hold, as in go language
basic data type are:
(1).  Numbers
(2).  Booleans
(3). String
-----------------------------------------------
custom data type
custom type struct means user can defined the data type 

package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
   apps := []string{"samsung", "nokia", "iphone"}

   for i, app := range apps {
    fmt.Println(i, app)
   }
}


